> **Deprecated for new features.** Use self-hosted API (`backend/`, `lib/repositories/`). Keep only while `USE_LEGACY_SUPABASE=true`.

## Client services (`baller_app/lib/supabase/`)

- Pattern: class with `final SupabaseClient _supabase = Supabase.instance.client;`
- `court_services.dart` delegates court CRUD to `RepositoryProvider.courts` for dual-mode access
- Example `CourtServices.createCourt` inserts into `courts` with keys: `source`, `name`, `lat`, `lng`, `indoor`, `lights`, `has_markings`, `surface`, `hoops`, `address`
- Use `.insert({...}).select('id').single()` and `return res['id'] as String;`
- Prefer `_supabase.from(...)` consistently inside methods
- Wrap failures: `try/catch` → `throw Exception('Failed to <action>: $e')` (match `auth_service.dart`)

## Edge functions (`baller_app/supabase/functions/`)

- Config: `baller_app/supabase/config.toml` — `[edge_runtime]`, `[functions.get-upload-url]` (`verify_jwt = true`)
- Template: `get-upload-url/index.ts` + `deno.json`

```typescript
Deno.serve(async (req) => {
  try {
    const { filename } = await req.json();
